Some friendships are fleeting, while others stand the test of time.
Making new friends also requires effort and openness. Sometimes, we have to put ourselves out there and initiate conversations with people we find interesting or attractive. Other times, we may have to wait for others to approach us. Regardless of how we meet someone, it's important to approach each new friendship with an open mind and heart.
But making friends is only half the battle. Building strong and lasting relationships takes time, patience, and mutual respect. It involves listening actively, communicating openly, and supporting one another through thick and thin. In short, making friends is a process that requires both effort and intentionality. And once we find that special someone who understands and accepts us for who we are, it can be one of the most rewarding experiences of our lives.
So if you're looking to make new friends, don't be afraid to put yourself out there. Take the first step, whether it's striking up a conversation with a stranger or joining a group of people who share your interests. Remember, true friends are worth more than gold, and with a little bit of effort and determination, you can find them too.」

As the song came to an end, I looked up at Ray Manzarek, who was sitting beside me, lost in thought. "Do you tend to avoid drawing attention to yourself?" he asked again.
I nodded slowly. "Yes, I do. I find that the less attention I draw, the more focused I am on creating art. I prefer to keep my private life separate from my public persona, and I find that helps me stay true to myself and my music."
Ray nodded in agreement. "I understand," he said. "But sometimes, it's hard to resist the lure of the spotlight. After all, being famous is kind of a dream come true."
I chuckled. "Being famous isn't always easy, Ray. It comes with its own set of challenges and pressures. But I wouldn't trade it for anything. As long as I can make music and connect with people through my music, I'll be happy."」
